msgid ""
"Added ``-Wlifetime-safety-dangling-field`` to detect dangling field "
"references when stack memory escapes to class fields. This is part of ``-"
"Wlifetime-safety`` and detects cases where local variables or parameters are "
"stored in fields but outlive their scope. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:529
msgid ""
"Improved ``-Wassign-enum`` performance by caching enum enumerator values. "
"(#GH176454)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:531
msgid ""
"Fixed a false negative in ``-Warray-bounds`` where the warning was "
"suppressed when accessing a member function on a past-the-end array element. "
"(#GH179128)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:535
msgid ""
"Added a missing space to the FixIt for the ``implicit-int`` group of "
"diagnostics and made sure that only one such diagnostic and FixIt is emitted "
"per declaration group. (#GH179354)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:538
msgid ""
"Fixed the Fix-It insertion point for ``expected ';' after alias "
"declaration`` when parsing alias declarations involving a token-split ``>>`` "
"sequence (for example, ``using A = X<int>>;``). (#GH184425)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:542
msgid ""
"Fixed incorrect ``implicitly deleted`` diagnostic for explicitly deleted "
"candidate function. (#GH185693)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:545
msgid ""
"The ``-Wloop-analysis`` warning has been extended to catch more cases of "
"variable modification inside lambda expressions (#GH132038)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:548
msgid ""
"Clang now emits ``-Wsizeof-pointer-memaccess`` when snprintf/vsnprintf use "
"the sizeof the destination buffer(dynamically allocated) in the len "
"parameter(#GH162366)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:551
msgid ""
"Added ``-Wmodule-map-path-outside-directory`` (off by default) to warn on "
"header and umbrella directory paths that use ``..`` to refer outside the "
"module directory in module maps found via implicit search (``-fimplicit-"
"module-maps``). This does not affect module maps specified explicitly via ``-"
"fmodule-map-file=``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:557
msgid ""
"Honour ``[[maybe_unused]]`` attribute on private fields. ``-Wunused-private-"
"field`` no longer emits a warning for annotated private fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:561
msgid ""
"Improved ``-Wgnu-zero-variadic-macro-arguments`` to suggest using "
"``__VA_OPT__`` if the current language version supports it(#GH188624)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:564
msgid ""
"Clang now emits an error when implicitly casting a complex type to a built-"
"in vector type. (#GH186805)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:566
msgid ""
"Added ``-Wnonportable-include-path-separator`` (off by default) to catch "
"#include directives that use backslashes as a path separator. The warning "
"includes a FixIt to change all the backslashes to forward slashes, so that "
"the code can automatically be made portable to other host platforms that "
"don't support backslashes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:572
msgid ""
"Clang now explains why template deduction fails for explicit template "
"arguments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:574
msgid ""
"No longer emitting a ``-Wpre-c2y-compat`` or extension diagnostic about use "
"of octal literals with a ``0o`` prefix, and no longer emitting a ``-"
"Wdeprecated-octal-literals`` diagnostic for use of octal literals without a "
"``0o`` prefix, when the literal is expanded from a macro defined in a system "
"header. (#GH192389)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:580
msgid ""
"Improved error recovery for missing semicolons after class members. Clang "
"now avoids skipping subsequent valid declarations when their previous decl "
"is missing semicolon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:583
msgid "Removed the body of lambdas from some diagnostic messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:585
msgid ""
"Fixed false positive host-device mismatch errors in discarded `if constexpr` "
"branches for CUDA/HIP; such calls are now correctly skipped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:588
msgid ""
"Clang now errors when a function declaration aliases a variable or vice "
"versa. (#GH195550)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:590
msgid ""
"Added ``-Wattribute-alias`` to diagnose type mismatches between an alias and "
"its aliased function. (#GH195550)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:592
msgid ""
"The diagnostics around ``__block`` now explain why a variable cannot be "
"marked ``__block``. (#GH197213)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:594
msgid ""
"Extended ``-Wnonportable-include-path`` to warn about trailing whitespace "
"and dots in ``#include`` paths. (#GH190610)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:596
msgid ""
"Clang now emits error when attribute is missing closing ``]]`` followed by "
"``;;``. (#GH187223)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:598
msgid ""
"Clang now rejects inline asm constraints and clobbers that contain an "
"embedded null character, instead of silently truncating them. (#GH173900)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:602
msgid "Improvements to Clang's time-trace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:605
msgid "Improvements to Coverage Mapping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:607
msgid "[MC/DC] Nested expressions are handled as individual MC/DC expressions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:608
msgid ""
"\"Single byte coverage\" now supports branch coverage and can be used "
"together with ``-fcoverage-mcdc``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:610
msgid ""
"Consteval member functions are no longer emitted in coverage mappings, "
"matching the existing behavior for free consteval functions. (#GH164448)"
msgstr ""

